{"parentUuid":"f9dfab04-2f1a-4285-8ea8-598d494ef256","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"c0b03e15-90c9-485f-acd0-bfcd3b62cd3e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01THnR31pZZxdogy31dGunnJ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Agent Plugins\n2\t\n3\tCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire, modeled after `obra/superpowers`.\n4\t\n5\tThis repo is a shared plugin collection for:\n6\t\n7\t- Codex\n8\t- Claude\n9\t- OpenCode\n10\t- Cursor\n11\t- Gemini\n12\t\n13\t## What You Get\n14\t\n15\t- Cross-agent skills for Entire workflows\n16\t- Root Gemini extension files at `gemini-extension.json` and `GEMINI.md`\n17\t- A Codex plugin package at `plugins/entire`\n18\t- A Cursor plugin manifest at `.cursor-plugin/`\n19\t- Install docs and manifests per agent platform\n20\t- A consistent handoff workflow across Codex, Claude, OpenCode, Cursor, and Gemini\n21\t\n22\t## Skills\n23\t\n24\t### `session-handoff`\n25\t\n26\tReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n27\t\n28\tCurrent behavior:\n29\t\n30\t- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n31\t- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n32\t- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n33\t- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n34\t- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n35\t- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n36\t- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n37\t- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n38\t\n39\t### `explain`\n40\t\n41\tTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n42\t\n43\tCurrent behavior:\n44\t\n45\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n46\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n47\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n48\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n49\t\n50\t### `search`\n51\t\n52\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n53\t\n54\tCurrent behavior:\n55\t\n56\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n57\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n58\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n59\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n60\t\n61\t## Installation\n62\t\n63\tInstall the agent that matches your workflow from its marketplace, manifest, or install-doc entrypoint:\n64\t\n65\t### Claude Code\n66\t\n67\tUse `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`.\n68\t\n69\t### Codex\n70\t\n71\tUse `plugins/entire/.codex-plugin/plugin.json`.\n72\t\n73\t### OpenCode\n74\t\n75\tUse the package-based flow in `.opencode/INSTALL.md`.\n76\t\n77\t### Cursor\n78\t\n79\tUse `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.\n80\t\n81\t### Gemini\n82\t\n83\tUse `gemini-extension.json` and `GEMINI.md`.\n84\t\n85\t## Quick Start\n86\t\n87\tNatural language examples:\n88\t\n89\t- \"hand off this session\"\n90\t- \"hand off the codex session\"\n91\t- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n92\t- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n93\t- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n94\t- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n95\t- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n96\t- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n97\t- \"have we done this before?\"\n98\t\n99\t## Checkpoint Resolution\n100\t\n101\tCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n102\t\n103\t1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n104\t2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n105\t3. nearby local clone\n106\t"}]},"uuid":"705bd004-94fb-438d-a497-ede61c419b8f","timestamp":"2026-04-10T20:30:42.036Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/alisha/Projects/agent-plugins/README.md","content":"# Agent Plugins\n\nCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire, modeled after `obra/superpowers`.\n\nThis repo is a shared plugin collection for:\n\n- Codex\n- Claude\n- OpenCode\n- Cursor\n- Gemini\n\n## What You Get\n\n- Cross-agent skills for Entire workflows\n- Root Gemini extension files at `gemini-extension.json` and `GEMINI.md`\n- A Codex plugin package at `plugins/entire`\n- A Cursor plugin manifest at `.cursor-plugin/`\n- Install docs and manifests per agent platform\n- A consistent handoff workflow across Codex, Claude, OpenCode, Cursor, and Gemini\n\n## Skills\n\n### `session-handoff`\n\nReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n\n### `explain`\n\nTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n\n### `search`\n\nSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the agent that matches your workflow from its marketplace, manifest, or install-doc entrypoint:\n\n### Claude Code\n\nUse `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`.\n\n### Codex\n\nUse `plugins/entire/.codex-plugin/plugin.json`.\n\n### OpenCode\n\nUse the package-based flow in `.opencode/INSTALL.md`.\n\n### Cursor\n\nUse `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.\n\n### Gemini\n\nUse `gemini-extension.json` and `GEMINI.md`.\n\n## Quick Start\n\nNatural language examples:\n\n- \"hand off this session\"\n- \"hand off the codex session\"\n- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n- \"have we done this before?\"\n\n## Checkpoint Resolution\n\nCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n\n1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n3. nearby local clone\n","numLines":106,"startLine":1,"totalLines":106}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f9dfab04-2f1a-4285-8ea8-598d494ef256","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/agent-plugins","sessionId":"ba833b9a-5a6d-4987-baa5-2f1dd001ad2e","version":"2.1.101","gitBranch":"main","slug":"async-stargazing-ember"}
